package.name: kdelibs3
package.summary: kdelibs3: Collective Update for several minor glitches
package.description: This is a collective update for 10.1 that fixes the following issues: - fix kdirwatch inducted memory corruption, often seen as Kate crashing during save (#188527) - fix Konqueror remote triggerable crash (#192393) - fix Kate crash in Kdevelop when closing all open tabs (#191819) - fix drag and drop pulls kdecache copy but not real file (#186501) - fix KDE defaults to weak cipher with POP3s (#181169) - translate ACL strings (#180268) - integrate print preview patch (#133246) - make khtml smooth scrolling acceptable (#175741) - fix kerberos handling for kprinter (#154334) - complete OpenDocument mime type icons (#166917) - only show kresources in KDE (#170681) - don't crash khtml on deep importNode with unsupported type (#209387) - evaluate scripts in in the right context (#209390)
